# Meta-Rules for This Repository

These rules apply when an agent is editing files inside the `engineering-standards` repository itself, editing the standards, not a project that consumes them.

## Tone and Writing Rules

- Maintain the tone and writing rules defined in `AGENTS.md` at all times.
- MUST NOT use em dashes, en dashes, or any forbidden word listed in `docs/conventions/shared/writing-style.md` in any generated content, documentation, or code comment.
- All diagrams in markdown files MUST use Mermaid syntax in a fenced code block. Never use ASCII art.

## Rule Integrity

- MUST NOT remove a rule from any convention file without adding a corresponding entry in `CHANGELOG.md` in the same commit.
- MUST NOT downgrade a `MUST` rule to a `SHOULD` rule without a CHANGELOG entry and a rationale in the convention file.
- MUST NOT add a rule without verifying it does not conflict with an existing rule in another convention file.

## AGENTS.md Size Limit

`AGENTS.md` MUST remain under 150 lines. If it exceeds 150 lines, extract detail to a convention file and link to it.

## Convention File Index

Update the convention file index table in `AGENTS.md` whenever a new convention file is added or renamed.

## Decision Index

When adding a new decision in `docs/decisions/`, add a row to `docs/decisions/README.md` with the canonical convention path in the same commit.

## Templates

When changing a convention that affects project-specific templates, update the corresponding file in `docs/templates/`.

Project-specific content (ubiquitous language, feature inventories, exception lists) does NOT belong in convention files. It belongs in the project repository using the templates in `docs/templates/`.

## Code Examples

Every new rule that can be illustrated with a code example MUST include both a `// GOOD:` and a `// BAD:` example. C# examples MUST omit `namespace` and `using` directives. Use `sealed` on all concrete types.
